      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE ART OF SUCCESS (11) was beaten into second as a hot favourite in her first two starts off a spell but got the win she deserved last start at this circuit and distance, coming from this row and arriving 9 metres ahead of the runner-up. Draws wider but is race fit now so can strike again. RONZEL MICKY (3) continued a strong run of recent form and deserved her victory last start, leading and scoring by 1.4 metres at this circuit and distance. Should push forward again from this nice draw so is capable of another big performance. MAGGACIS (7) broke when fourth last time but won three in a row here prior, two of those when off this barrier. Worth another chance. ROYAL SAXON (2) led and stuck on when runner-up to The Art of Success last start. Draws to be competitive again.",
